reviews:
If you're looking for cool, soft, stretchy, super comfortable socks, look no further! I got the gray ones (they were cheaper than blk which I really wanted) but these are practically black anyway. Perfect for under office pants. Yes, they have a slight seam on top of the foot. Doesn't bother me. The foot is cushioned, but not super thick. I'm thinking these will last longer because of the cushioning and will not show holes under the ball of my feet. The length goes up past my ankle but nothing like crew socks would. My feet always get quite hot, but with these socks my feet can breathe.
They look small when you unwrap them, but they're quite stretchy. I'd advise hanging them to dry. Avoid the dryer on these.
My feet are delighted, and I would highly recommend!

review_title: A really sweet top, well made--washes well.
reviews:
Absolutely love this top--it would be perfect for summer-- it's very light, almost but not quite semi transparent, and has lots of swing/width at the bottom.
I liked it so much, I ordered the grey, the blue as well as waiting on the orange.
I'm a large/xl, and xl fits well--my arms are rather muscular so the sleeves aren't too tight for me as I've seen in other reviews--my problem area is my middle age lady middle.
I washed the first one--the black in the washing machine and figured--"nothing ventured, nothing gained", "do this for the people, HD", and put it in the dryer. You're welcome. :)
If it shrunk at all, it was very little--so that was enough to send me back to get the other colours I wanted. It's good to get what you like while it's in stock.
Some folks have mentioned the prominent middle seam, which is noticeable because the fabric is somewhat see-thru, the top has buttons, and you can't get buttons without making seams--thus--there's a middle seam. I actually really like the middle seam--it's slightly darker in some colours, and it looks nice. It's also very well sewed--double sewed flat so it shouldn't come apart. Another reason why I love this top.
Yeah, I got Morange, too.

review_title: Hard to tell without trying it on
reviews: Liked the look of it, so decided to try it. I usually take an XL in tops, but I have a large bust, so I ordered this in 2XL, in the dark grey. The colour and style looked exactly like the picture. The front hit me at upper thigh - longer than a t-shirt, but definitely too short for me to wear as a dress. But the overall fit was...odd. On the pro side, it was very billowy without making me feel like I was wearing a shapeless potato sack. Was fitted at the top and then flowed out. The seams, buttons, etc were all good quality. On the con side, I found the area around the seam where the arm is attached to the body of the top (so the shoulder/armpit area) weirdly tight compared to the rest of the top. The neck was a little wide, so my bra straps were visible. And although the back was very drapey and billowy, I found the front clung a bit to my belly. I waffled back and forth on whether to keep it, but in the end, I decided to return it. I think it would have looked better if I had a smaller chest. But one of those things where I think it's hard to tell until you actually have it on.
